race.comment: BLACK MINTO (1) went forward and proved too strong here, scoring by 4.5 lengths over this distance. Has to skip over from a wide gate today but the 3kg remains handy and she can go on with the job. NEOCLASSICISM (4) began awkwardly and covered ground here last time. His win this grade prior was good and he maps better today. A chance to bounce. DEEP DRIVE (7) ran a good relative number winning her Maiden here on the turf. She will be better for that and just has to take to the poly surface to feature. EASTOWN (5) has a wide gate to manage but his effort here two back reads well. Keep safe. TARADALE (8) has the blinkers on again and won't be far away.
